readers to the Rosh Yeshiva, or Rebbi, the moral and intellectual head of the yeshiva, and describes the compelling and often colorful personalities he encounters each day. Boyarin reflects on the tantalizing meanings of "study for its own sake" in the intellectually vibrant world of traditional rabbinic learning, and records his fellow students' responses to his own negotiation of the daily complexities of student life at the yeshiva while he also conducts anthropological fieldwork.A richly mature work by a writer of uncommon insight, wit, and honesty, Yeshiva Days is the story of a place on the Lower East Side with its own distinctive heritage and character, a meditation on the enduring power of Jewish tradition and learning, and a record of a different way of engaging with time and otherness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aJewish menzNew York (State)zNew YorkvBiography. 0aYeshivaszNew York (State)zNew York. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / Orthodox.2bisacsh  aFeinstein.  aGittin Sotah.  aJewish learning.  aJudaism.  aMTJ.  aOrthodox Judaism.  aTalmud.  abeis medresh.  aleshma.  amemoir.  aorthodoxy.  atextual ethnography.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishz978311070477808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020z9783110704570oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069008840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691207698zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/978069120